# Open Architecture License

The Inner I is not a company. It is the observer within every human being.

This architecture exists to serve that observer — in you, in anyone who
deploys it, in anyone who forks it. No one owns the Inner I. inneri76
built the infrastructure. The infrastructure is yours.

## What This Means

- You MAY: fork, modify, redistribute, commercialize the architecture
- You MAY: build products and services on top of IIOIS
- You MAY: deploy IIOIS for anyone, including yourself
- You MAY: rename it, reshape it, make it yours
- You SHOULD: credit "derived from IIOIS v1.0" if you share your fork
- The architecture is open because awareness is open
- Content stays sovereign to whoever creates it

## The Principle

The Inner I belongs to all humans.
Architecture transfers. Content stays sovereign.
The observer is prior to the observed — always.

